Author: Mudae#0807
Content:
**$disable**: ($d) Disable series for your rolls. *$disable Re:Zero*
**$disablelist**: ($dl) Your list of disabled characters. See `$disable`
**$serverdisable**: (MOD, $sd) Disable up to 1,000 characters for the whole server.
**$serverdisablelist**: ($sdl) Server list of disabled characters. See `$serverdisable`
**$togglewestern**: Completely disable western animanga characters for your rolls.
**$toggleirl**: Completely disable characters from the bundle `Real Life People` for your rolls.
**$disabletag**: ($dt) Disable characters having specific tags for your rolls. Wishes still enable them.
**$togglensfw**: (MOD) Completely disable NSFW series for the whole server.
**$toggledisturbing**: (MOD) Completely disable disturbing imagery series for the whole server.
**$togglechildtag**: (MOD) Completely disable characters having the `Child` and `Baby` tags ($tag child, $tag baby) for the whole server.
**$limroul**: (GAMEMODE 2) Define the number of different characters you can roll in __each roulette__ (by disabling the less popular characters). *$limroul 7000 7000 5000 5000*
**$servlimroul**: (MOD, GAMEMODE 2) Define the number of different characters you can roll in __each roulette__ (by disabling the less popular characters) for your whole server. *$servlimroul 7000 7000 5000 5000*
**$disabledm**: Make your $disablelist and your $antidisablelist private or public again.
**$hideinfodisable**: Disable the üö´ emoji indicating the character is disabled for __YOUR__ rolls ($im or $mmi)
**option x**: Only display characters you disabled. *$mmx*
**option x+**: Display characters you disabled along with characters you didn't disable. *$mmx+*
**option x-**: Only display characters you didn't disable. *$mmx-*
**$toggleplayerpremium**: (Player Premium) Disable/enable your Player Premium on this server instance.
**$qs**: Save your current wishlist, disablelist or antidisablelist. *$qs wl*
**$ql**: Load your saved wishlist, disablelist or antidisablelist. *$ql wl*

Author: Mudae#0807
Content:
Syntax: $disable <series to disable>
This will remove from your rolls all the characters having this series as their main series.
For multiple series, separate them by a $

To remove a series from your **$disablelist**, use **$enable** <series> or $enableall
$disablelist options: **d** (details), **v** (vanilla), **s** (DM)
Use $disabledel ($dd) to autodelete your $disable message

Use **$disabletag** to disable characters having specific tags.
Available for the following tags: child, baby, child-like, animal, anthropomorphic animal, species, character class, spider, triggering content, disturbing imagery, clown
Wishes enable characters disabled by $disable and $disabletag, but **not** those disabled by $togglewestern and $toggleirl

Your rolls can't be reduced below **7,000** characters available for each animanga roulette ($wa, $ha) and below **5,000** characters for each game roulette ($wg, $hg).

Kakeraloots (up to +15, depends on the number of 'disable more' loots), kakeratower and premium can decrease these values (up to 2,000 characters per pool). Series below these limit (not the entire bundle) are not disabled.

Author: Mudae#0807
Content:
Syntax: **$ima** <series to search>

Type **$s flags** for the list of filters.

**$imaq!** <series> if you want to return the list instead of one series.
**$ima** <series 1>$<series 2> for multiple series.
**$ima** <series>$<page> to jump to the page.
**$imab** <series> for the bundle list of the series.
**$imap** <series> = <character(s)> to search by character name.
**$imae** <series> = <tag(s)> to search by tag.
**$ima&** <bundle 1>$<bundle 2> to not search by series overlapping.
**$imaq+** <series> (or $imaq- <series>) to only search for series containing a part starting (or ending) exactly by your request.
**$ima?** <series> to display all aliases, including those from other countries, and the definition if available.
**$ima*** to only display characters whose main series is this one.
**$ima*-** to only display characters whose main series is not this one.
**$ima*+** to display characters regardless of their main series (useful for bundles).

Ex.: $imawo attack on titan

Author: Mudae#0807
Content:
Syntax: **$likem <series>**
This will add the series to your list of liked series.
For multiple series, separate them with a $

- **$lmp <position> <series>**: insert a series at a specific position (and move down others)
- **$lmr <series>**: remove a series.
- **$lmclear**: clear your list after confirmation.

- **$ml**: get your list. Flags: **a** (animanga roulette), **g** (video game bundle), **j** (anime bundle), **v** (visual novel bundle), **k** (manhwa bundle), **o** (western bundle), **c** (comics bundle), **h** (hentai bundle), **==** (alphabetical display), <series>
Example: $mlg

Author: Mudae#0807
Content:
Syntax: **$tuarrange <category> <category> ...**
Effect: arrange the order of the categories for your **$tu** command.
Categories not specified in the command will be hidden.

List of categories:
**claim, rolls, daily, keys, kakerareact, kakerapower, kakerainfo, kakerastock, rt, dk, pokemon, vote, rollsreset, jump**
*jump* is used to jump a line (up to 10 jump)

Example (default value): $ta claim rolls daily jump kakerareact kakerapower kakerainfo kakerastock jump rt dk vote
